---
source: crates/carta/tests/golden_e2e.rs
expression: output
---
<span id="section"></span>
= !!! =

A heading that slugs to nothing falls back to a reserved identifier.

<span id="section-1"></span>
= ??? =

Another empty slug is disambiguated against the fallback.

<span id="foo"></span>
= Foo =

A base identifier.

<span id="foo-1"></span>
= Foo =

A repeat gains a numeric suffix.

<span id="foo-1-1"></span>
= Foo 1 =

A title that already carries the suffix is disambiguated further.

<span id="i-here"></span>
= İ here =

A dotted capital I lowercases to a letter plus a combining mark that the identifier drops.

<span id="wordend"></span>
= WordͅEnd =

A letter-like combining mark is not a letter and is dropped from the identifier.
